<P>
   RUSSIA-BOMBINGS (Moscow) _ Apartment dwellers band together,
vigilante style, to run round-the-clock patrols of their buildings
and foot and vehicle traffic outside _ all to protect themselves
from terrorist bombs. By David Filipov. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   BEOGRAD-DOT-COM (Undated) _ During the bombing of Yugoslavia,
Beograd.com was the way Serbs found out where the bombs were
landing. Now that the war is over, the web site has become a
national chat room for political discussions. By John Donnelly.
1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   FOREIGN-JOURNAL (London) _ The mystery is over: Chief Inspector
Morse dies. With him will go one of the most popular mystery series
to have run on public television. By Kevin Cullen. 750 words. (i
and e coding)
</P>
