times over the next 10 days, both teams with an eye on the NL East
championship. As they prepare for the crucial stretch, the teams
are using extremely different pitching philosophies. The Mets have
used a six-man starting rotation in recent weeks and have been far
more reliant on their bullpen than the Braves, who have had bullpen
problems and have relied on the strong starting pitching of Greg
Maddux and Kevin Millwood. A look at the pitching staffs of the
teams heading into the key stretch. (Stinson, Atlanta
