<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The good, the bad, the best of 15,000 health-related sites
 &HT;    By M.A.J. McKenna
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A reliable site with a reputable name is the Merck Manual
Online, at www.merck.com/pubs/mmanual. In print form, the Merck
Manuals have guided health professionals and parents for 100 years.
The cyber format mimics the paper version: Look up a problem with
the search function and click through the results it delivers.
Searching for ``measles,'' for instance, finds 24 mentions in the
manual, including recommended times for childhood immunizations,
descriptions of symptoms in an infected child and potential
complications from mild to dangerous.
</P>
<P>
   _M.A.J. McKenna writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
