</P>
<P>
   Ms. Telen said Mrs. Gorbachev was well aware of the resentment
against her felt by many Russians. But she herself was never
bitter. ``She realized that people had been used to different
women, different traditions, different leaders,'' said Ms. Telen.
``She understood it. It hurt her of course, but I never heard her
be mean or bitter about it.''
</P>
