   (NYT25) HOUSTON -- Sept. 20, 1999 -- BKL-COOPER-PROFILE-2, 09-20
-- Cynthia Cooper, the superstar point guard of the Houston Comets,
after defeating the New York Liberty in the finals of the Women's
National Basketball Association on September 5. Cooper, 36, has
written a new autobiography, ``She Got Game: My Personal Odyssey.''
``It's really about living life to the fullest,'' she says. ``I
want people to read this book and to be inspired by it.'' (Michelle
V. Agins/New York Times Photo)
