<P>
   (NYT7) UNDATED -- Sept. 20, 1999 -- JONES-PLAGIARISM, 09-20 --
James Mackay's new work, ``I Have Not Yet Begun to Fight: A life of
John Paul Jones,'' right, is the first full-length biography of the
Scottish-born American naval hero in 40 years. After questions from
The New York Times, however, Mackay's publisher has halted the book
for a check on similarities to the last major Jones biography,
published in 1959 by the eminent American historian Samuel Eliot
Morison, left. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) TARABORO, N.C. -- Sept. 20, 1999 -- HURRICANE-CAROLINAS,
09-20 --Brittney Bryant, 6, of Princeville, N.C. , plays on Monday
in the gymnasium at Tarboro High School, where some 3,000 people
are being shelter after their homes were flooded by Hurricane
Floyd. More rain was expected Monday night which authorities feared
may worsen flooding in the eastern North Carolina region, possibly
delaying the return of over 10,000 people to their homes. (Stephen
Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) BOSTON -- Sept. 20, 1999 -- WALKMAN-REVOLUTION, 09-20 --
Emily Brady, 19, a student at Boston University, listens to the
``Beatles'' on her Sony Walkman while strolling up Massachusetts
Avenue last week. This month marks the 20th anniversary of the
introduction of the Sony Walkman, a device which revolutionized the
personal electronics industry. (Pat Greenhouse/Boston Globe Photo)
