<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 21
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IRAQ-U.N.-SANCTIONS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Sept. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Sept. 19,
about a call by the senior United Nations official in Iraq for the
immediate lifting of many sanctions on that country misstated the
duration of the sanctions. They have been in place since Iraq
invaded Kuwait in 1990, not since the Persian Gulf war in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   BC-WEB-INVENTOR-PROFILE-NYT (moved on Sunday, Sept. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Sept. 19,
about Tim Berners-Lee, the creator of the World Wide Web,
misspelled the surname of a freelance writer who collaborated with
him on a new book. The writer is Mark Fischetti, not Fishetti.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BACON-MOVIES-NYT (moved on Friday, Sept. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Sept. 17,
about the actor Kevin Bacon and the progress of his career
misstated the given name of his father, a prominent urban planner.
It is Edmund, not Robert.
</P>
</TEXT>
