<SLUG> BC-CHURCHSHOOTING-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DOCTOR HAD PRESCRIBED ANTI-DEPRESSANT FOR CHURCH SHOOTER
</HEADLINE>
 (EDS: Name Marjorie Poche carries an accent on the e. Resending to
fix garble.) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
By KATHY SANDERS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ A doctor had prescribed the anti-depressant
drug Prozac for Larry Gene Ashbrook, but investigators are unsure
whether he was taking it when he killed seven people and then
himself in a Fort Worth church last week, police said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Fort Worth's Lt. Mark Krey, who is heading the investigation
into the largest mass shooting in the city's history, said police
have found a Prozac vial in Ashbrook's name and want to ask doctors
why it was prescribed.
</P>
<P>
   Krey said Ashbrook, 47, may have slipped past the brink of
sanity after his father died in July.
</P>
<P>
   ``The level of paranoia within his life had advanced to an
extreme stage,'' he said. ``We're investigating the possibility
that with the death of his father, Mr. Ashbrook stopped taking
medication. We believe when he lost his father, who was his anchor
to reality and his caretaker to ensure he took his medication, he
lost any connection to reality.''
</P>
<P>
   Also on Monday, police said a homemade pipe bomb exploded in
Wedgwood Baptist Church with enough velocity to send a piece of
shrapnel hurtling 80 feet before slicing through a wall and landing
in the hallway outside the sanctuary, Krey said.
</P>
<P>
   But rather than blasting out into a sanctuary where more than
150 worshippers were taking part in a youth service, shrapnel shot
toward the ceiling and then rained down.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are very blessed in the manner in which it detonated ... or
it would have caused serious bodily injury,'' Krey said.
</P>
<P>
   FBI officials said they found nine vials of prescription drugs
for Jack Ashbrook in the family home in suburban Forest Hill as
well as a diary in which the father documented his pill use, said
spokeswoman Marjorie Poche. It is unclear where the Prozac was
found.
</P>
<P>
   ``The writing changed in the last couple of weeks of the diary.
It's only speculation, but (Larry Ashbrook) may have started taking
his father's medication,'' she said. ``Either that or he started
recording when his father took the pills. ...''
</P>
<P>
   The final three of his seven victims were laid to rest on
Monday, but Ashbrook's body remained unclaimed at the Tarrant
County Medical Examiner's Office.
</P>
<P>
   Aaron Ashbrook, his brother, said the family is finalizing
funeral arrangements, but declined to comment further.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think there probably has been more said than there needs to
be, and a lot of it's untrue,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   He declined to elaborate.
</P>
<P>
   ``It wouldn't make any difference,'' he said. ``I think the
damage has already been done.''
</P>
<P>
   Investigators classified information on Monday from nearly 70
depositions taken the night of the shooting, reinterviewed the
wounded and tried to trace Ashbrook's final, fatal steps.
</P>
<P>
   ``Investigators are going though a number of depositions to
determine the exact sequence of events,'' said homicide Sgt. Dave
Loftis. ``We want to know, first of all, specifically what happened
and how everything went down that day.''
</P>
<P>
   But the search for the most asked questions _ what set Ashbrook
off and why did he choose Wedgwood _ may never pay off.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have any motive right now,'' Loftis said. ``I don't
know if we'll ever have an answer to those questions. If we can, we
certainly will get them. It's like any of those senseless acts of
violence, there aren't any answers. And can any motive explain it
and make sense of it?''
</P>
<P>
   In his writings, Ashbrook details a vast, unspecified conspiracy
against him by law enforcement. His brother described him to Wise
County sheriff's deputies as a paranoid schizophrenic.
</P>
<P>
   Krey said Ashbrook apparently was such a loner that few people
have been found to help explain his activities.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe we won't find anybody because there is nobody to
find. And that is consistent with the mental illness he appeared to
be afflicted with,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Inside the church, Ashbrook fired all six rounds from a
.380-caliber semiautomatic gun, then fired up to 50 more shots from
a Ruger 9mm semi-automatic pistol, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Six of his seven victims died from gunshot wounds to the head,
autopsy reports show. The seventh was fatally shot in the back.
</P>
<P>
   Ashbrook shot himself with the 9mm, police said. He apparently
was alive in a back pew when paramedics rushed into the sanctuary,
but was pronounced dead a short time later, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Ashbrook's victims were Christi Beckel, 14; Shawn Brown, 23;
Susan Kimberly Jones, 23; Cassandra F. Griffin, 14; Joseph ``Joey''
D. Ennis, 14; Sydney R. Browning, 36; and Justin M. Ray, 17.
</P>
<P>
   Ray and a woman separately videotaped Ashbrook's rampage, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Officials in Forest Hill said Ashbrook also may have made a
futile effort to contaminate the city of Forest Hill's water
system.
</P>
<P>
   ``He put concrete in the commodes and, working for the city, I
wanted to make sure he didn't do something else,'' said Forest Hill
Public Works Director Michael Duehring.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted to make sure he did not contaminate our water system.
I can't go any further than that and tell you what he did, but he
didn't do any damage.''
</P>
<P>
   FBI officials inspected plumbing in Ashbrook's home Thursday
after the concerns were voiced. They did not, Poche said, consider
it a serious threat.
</P>
<P>
   ``The agent said it looked like he was just trying to mess up
the inside of the house,'' said agent Marjorie Poche. ``The agent
who was out there said he had ripped off the shower head and neck
and put one of those paper cones and a quart of motor oil to back
down into the pipes. He said it was stuck in there still.''
</P>
<P>
   (Staff writer Bob Mahlburg contributed to this report.)
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
